    "title": "Introduction to Accounting",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "text": "What is Accounting?"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Accounting is the process of recording, classifying, summarizing, and interpreting financial transactions. It helps businesses understand their financial performance and position."
      },
      {
        "type": "sub_heading",
        "text": "Why is Accounting Important?"
      },
      {
        "type": "bullet_list",
        "items": [
          "Records financial transactions.",
          "Measures profit and loss.",
          "Helps in decision making.",
          "Maintains legal compliance."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "note",
        "text": "Accounting is often called the language of business."
      },
      {
        "type": "tip",
        "text": "Remember the four keywords: Record, Classify, Summarize, Interpret."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "contentId": 2,
    "subjectId": 101,
